-- Hong Kong shares up on bank earnings, HSCE has best week in months  
-- By Natalie Thomas
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 04:10AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, March 28 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares rose on Friday on the back of strong bank earnings, helping the benchmark index have its best weekly performance since mid-February.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed up 1.1 percent at 22065.53 points. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong closed up 1.3 percent, contributing to its best weekly performance since the week ending Nov. 22. Industrial and Commercial Bank of China <1398.HK> climbed 1.7 percent after the bank announced a higher-than-expected net profit increase for the fourth quarter. [ID:nL4N0MO275]  Hong Kong tech shares clawed back some of Thursday's losses, pulled up by online heavyweight Tencent Holdings Ltd. <0700.HK>, which followed up the previous day's 6.3 percent tumble with a 2.4 percent gain.